  "body": "- [ ] I've [opened a support ticket](https://trufflesuite.zendesk.com/hc/en-us/requests/new) before filing this issue.\r\n\r\n---------------------------\r\n\r\n## Issue\r\n\r\nIt should revert the custom error, works in Remix VM but not with Web3+Truffle in Node.js, tested on a local Ganache network and Avalanche Testnet. Only seems to be able to revert string-based custom errors, if I pass an integer or something that is not a string it gives me the out of bounds error.\r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n```solidity\r\n\r\n// SPDX-License-Identifier: GPL-3.0\r\npragma solidity ^0.8.4;\r\n\r\n\r\ncontract TestToken {\r\n    error InsufficientBalance(uint256 withdrawAmount);\r\n\r\n    function transfer(uint256 amount) pure public {\r\n        if (amount > 1000)\r\n            revert InsufficientBalance({ withdrawAmount: amount });\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\n\r\nIt should revert the custom error, works in Remix VM but not with Web3+Truffle in Node.js, tested on a local Ganache network and Avalanche Testnet. Only seems to be able to revert string-based custom errors, if I pass an integer or something that is not a string it gives me the out of bounds error.\r\n\r\n## Actual Results\r\n\r\nGet the following error in Node.js:\r\n```\r\nError: data out-of-bounds (length=0, offset=32, code=BUFFER_OVERRUN, version=abi/5.0.7)\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Operating System: Ubuntu 20.04 LTS\r\n* Ethereum client: Ganache/Avalanche\r\n* Truffle version (`truffle version`): \"@truffle/hdwallet-provider\": \"^2.1.8\"\r\n* node version (`node --version`): v18.13.0\r\n* npm version (`npm --version`): 8.19.3\r\n",
